    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="0">
            <title>Coolant Heater (if equipped)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If servicing a leaky coolant heater, replace O-ring on heater assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place non-petroleum base lubricant around O-ring area and install into crankcase. Orient
                    electrical connector so that it is facing downward (6 o'clock position).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the 5/32 in hex socket head cap screw to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_204.xml" xrefid="t2650903" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replenish coolant level if only servicing coolant heater.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
